# Phase-3 G20-A3: re-track the browser-bundle artifact directory under
# `bindings/napi/dist/browser/` (carved out from the global `dist/`
# exclusion above). The browser_target_bundle_size test pin reads the
# committed placeholder seed (47-byte gzipped wasm) + README; CI's
# wasm-browser.yml workflow replaces the seed with the real production
# bundle on push. Without re-tracking, fresh CI clones see no artifact
# and the test pin fails. Same re-tracking shape as
# `docs/SECURITY-POSTURE.md` (G11-A Wave 3a) +
# `docs/INVARIANT-COVERAGE.md` (Phase 2b G11-2b) +
# `docs/DSL-SPECIFICATION.md` (Phase 3 G19-D fp).
!bindings/napi/dist/
!bindings/napi/dist/browser/
!bindings/napi/dist/browser/benten_engine.wasm.gz
!bindings/napi/dist/browser/README.md

