# Default-untracked docs pending public rewrite (internal-audience in current form).
# Public surface is deliberately minimal: README, LICENSE-*, CONTRIBUTING, SECURITY,
# plus docs/QUICKSTART + docs/ARCHITECTURE + docs/ERROR-CATALOG + docs/GLOSSARY
# (and a HOW-IT-WORKS doc to be authored). Everything below stays local until
# rewritten for a public audience.
docs/VISION.md
docs/ENGINE-SPEC.md
# `docs/DSL-SPECIFICATION.md` re-tracked in Phase 3 G19-D wave-7: the
# G19-D worked example for the SUBSCRIBE handler-id-router is named
# from `docs/future/phase-3-backlog.md` (lines 655, 659, 895, 901) per
# HARD RULE rule-12 clause-(b) — destination MUST EXIST in fresh CI
# clones for the BELONGS-NAMED-NOW disposition to hold. Same re-tracking
# pattern as `docs/SECURITY-POSTURE.md` (G11-A Wave 3a) +
# `docs/INVARIANT-COVERAGE.md` + `docs/HOST-FUNCTIONS.md` (Phase 2b
# G11-2b) — public-rewrite-pending content stays as-is; visibility is
# what re-tracking restores.
docs/TRANSFORM-GRAMMAR.md
docs/FULL-ROADMAP.md
# `docs/SECURITY-POSTURE.md` re-tracked in G11-A Wave 3a DOC-REGRESSION:
# the `compromise_6_blake3_collision_resistance_note_in_security_posture`
# regression test (in `crates/benten-engine/tests/integration/
# compromises_regression.rs`) reads this file from the working tree, so
# fresh CI clones must contain it. The file's content stayed on disk
# locally between db5831f (default-untrack pass) and Wave 3a; re-tracking
# restores the public-clone visibility the regression test requires.
docs/PLATFORM-DESIGN.md
docs/BUSINESS-PLAN.md
# `docs/INVARIANT-COVERAGE.md` re-tracked in Phase 2b G11-2b: ships
# alongside the SANDBOX runtime so Inv-4 + Inv-7 active rows are
# discoverable in fresh CI clones. The
# `invariant_coverage_doc_lists_inv_4_and_inv_7_active` regression test
# reads it from the working tree.
# `docs/HOST-FUNCTIONS.md` re-tracked in Phase 2b G11-2b: operator-facing
# host-fn surface doc paired with the codegen TOML drift detectors
# (`host_functions_doc_drift_against_toml`,
# `host_functions_md_drift_against_toml`,
# `host_functions_doc_lists_every_codegen_entry`); fresh CI clones
# must carry it.
docs/BENCHMARKING.md
# `docs/future/*` (not `docs/future/`) so git descends into the dir +
# applies the per-file negations below. Track the phase-N backlog docs —
# they're cited from in-tree code as named-destinations for
# Phase-3-deferred items (per HARD RULE rule-1 clause-b:
# BELONGS-ELSEWHERE-NAMED + destination must EXIST). Other docs/future/
# exploratory drafts stay local-only.
docs/future/*
!docs/future/phase-2-backlog.md
!docs/future/phase-3-backlog.md
!docs/future/phase-4-backlog.md
!docs/future/kith-decentralized-identity.md
!docs/future/v1-gate-refactor.md
crates/benten-graph/benches/README.md
crates/README.md
bindings/README.md
tests/README.md

